dismissalText.commentary: Stuart Binny c †Mutumbami b Tiripano 77 (76b 6x4 2x6 92m) SR: 101.31

dismissalComment.html: Binny swings and edges it behind. Pushed full and wide outside off, Tiripano rolls his fingers across this cutter. Binny's balance is a mess as he looks to kitchen-sink it away. He can only manage an outside edge to Mutumbami. End of a rapid stand, the highest sixth-wicket stand for India

dismissalText.commentary: Robin Uthappa run out (Sikandar Raza) 0 (3b 0x4 0x6 6m) SR: 0

dismissalComment.html: a direct hit at the non-strikers' end and Uthappa is in trouble. They go to the TV umpire. Uthappa has to go, he bags a duck. He drops this full ball near short cover and calls for a risky single. Raza sprints to his right, swoops down on the ball and under-arm flicks it onto the furniture. Two wickets in two overs and India slip to 77 for 4

dismissalComment.html: another half-tracker, Raza goes for a pull and gifts his wicket. He makes a mess of the pull as he mistimes it in the air. Axar runs in from deep midwicket, flings himself forward and snaps it up. First ODI wicket for Harbhajan in four years

dismissalComment.html: Hami M falls. Alarming turn and bounce. Might have held up in the pitch as well. Hami M was surprised by it as he just chips it tamely to Tiwary at point off the outside half of the bat. Hami M yanked his bottom hand off the bat as he met the ball
Axar takes out Williams for a duck. He gives this more air outside off, grips in the surface and rips through the bat-pad gap to hit the top of middle and off. Zimbabwe fall behind in the chase
Binny strikes back! Dragged short, not much bite in it. It should have been put away, instead Sibanda mis-hits the pull. Harbhajan swallows it at mid-on. Good overhead catch

Binny rolls his fingers across this one. Mutumbai targets the leg side with a flick but ends up spooning a leading edge to Harbhajan at mid-off. He runs to his right and takes it. They check for a possible no-ball. Binny is okay

commentPreTextItems.html: Six to win off the last ball.
Dev: "Give Chigumbura the phone. Let him talk to Miandad!!"

commentTextItems.html: India edge Zimbabwe. Bhuvi hurls a yorker on a leg-stump line, down the track and driven to long-on. Chigumbura can't do a Miandad..

commentPostTextItems.html: That is that from this thriller. Do tune in for the second ODI on Sunday. Until then, this is Deivarayan Muthu saying phew..

Rayudu, Man of the Match: It was very tough to bat in the morning. Me and Ajju were batting well until he got out. I am happy that I took the responsibility today. I was just telling Binny to hold back a bit till the 42nd over as he couldn't afford to lose wickets then. Contributing to the team is more important.

Rahane, India captain: Rayudu batted really well because the wicket was not easy early on. The way he batted it was brilliant to see from the dressing room. We all knew 255 was a good score. We knew our fielding was good. Bhajji pa and Axar bowled well. I was looking to stay calm but inside I was nervous. It could have gone either way. Credit to both batsmen and bowlers.

Chigumbura, Zimbabwe captain: It was disappointing to lose the game after getting so close. It is something we can learn. I thought it was a good wicket to bat on, but we kept losing wickets. Losing wickets in groups made the difference today. It is also good to score runs and hopefully I can carry on and win for the team.
4:45pm Chigumbura's century marshalled a strong Zimbabwe response, but Bhuvneshwar held his nerve in the final over. His assortment of yorkers helped India defend ten off the last over.

The hosts were reduced to 47 for 2 in 12.2 overs. Enter Chigumbura. He put his side back on track with able contributions from Hamilton Masakadza and Raza, before kicking into a higher gear. He took it down to the last ball but could't pull the rug from under India's feet.
Harbhajan and Axar showed good control in the middle overs, Bhuvneshwar was accurate but Kulkarni and Binny strayed in lines and lengths, leaking runs. Do stick around for the presentation.
cricpolls: "@Dev: But looks like Bhuvi missed a call from Chetan Sharma."
Revanth: "So close, yet so far for Zimbabwe."
Balaji: "Encouraging win for inexperienced Indian team... good performances from Rayudu, Binny and Bhuvi... Encouraging display from Zimbabwe as well."
Damo: "Binny could fill in the jigsaw as the allrounder."

commentTextItems.html: low full toss outside off, flashes a drive straight to Rahane at the covers
Bhuvneshwar serves up a full toss outside off, skewered to long-off on the bounce. Chigumbura refuses a single
yorker on a leg-stump line, flicked to long leg
nails a yorker, just outside off. Makes room and drills it forcefully to deep cover

commentPreTextItems.html: Zimbabwe need ten off the final over. Rahane and Bhuvi have a chat.

commentTextItems.html: right in the blockhole on middle, clipped to long-on Chigumbura races across for the second

dismissalText.commentary: Graeme Cremer c Binny b Kulkarni 27 (36b 2x4 0x6 54m) SR: 75

commentTextItems.html: What have you done Cremer? Full toss outside the leg stump, he goes for a reverse-sweep and hits it right into the lap of  Binny at backward point. The wide has helped him get the wicket, but India needed Chigumbura's wicket
full toss on a leg-stump line, pushed to long-on. They hare across for a couple
short of a length and outside off, Cremer pulls it to wide long-on off the front foot. Tiwary is not quick enough and they take two

veering onto the pads, nudged to the leg side off an inside edge. Chigumbura gets to a century, back-to-back hundreds. He eases the helmet off his head, punches the air in delight and celebrates. WHADDA innings. Harare jiving with their captain...
sliding down leg, he can't connect with a flick. Wide called
Kulkarni pushes it too full and on middle, Creamer makes room and drills a drive to long-off
short and on a leg-stump line, cramping Chigumbura for room. Helped to long leg with a pull
Cremer brings out the scoop, a la Dougie Marillier. Full and on middle and leg, he scoops it away fine on the leg side, leaving the ball boy breaking into a catchy little jig as he collects the ball
another full toss, Chigumbura misses out. Tucked away to leg for only one
Bhuvneshwar turns to the slower ball outside off, dragged to long-on. Vijay runs to his left, dives forward but drops it
another low full toss, picked away off the toes and whipped to deep midwicket

commentPostTextItems.html: Aaram: "Excellent knock from Chigumbura. If he stays there till the end, Zimbabwe can win this."

commentTextItems.html: Bhuvneshwar hunts for a yorker but ends up bowling a full toss. Chigumbura sits back in the crease and smashes it to the left of long-on, one-bounce four

commentPreTextItems.html: santosh battula: "India's struggle in death overs continues..."

commentTextItems.html: full toss on middle and leg, clipped to long-on for a single
shortish and drifting down leg, helped to deep backward square leg with a pull

dismissalComment.html: Chibhabha gets Tiwary, umpire Tiffin's finger goes up. Reward for probing bowling. Pitched up, smacks Tiwary on the front pad bang in front of middle. Again, Tiwary did not move his feet much as he attempted a defensive push. This would have rattled the leg stump

headshotImage.caption: Robin Uthappa player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Robin Uthappa player page headshot cutout, 2021

headshotImage.caption: Robin Uthappa player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Robin Uthappa player page headshot cutout, 2021

headshotImage.caption: Brian Vitori player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Brian Vitori player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Robin Uthappa run out (Sikandar Raza) 0 (3b 0x4 0x6 6m) SR: 0

dismissalComment.html: a direct hit at the non-strikers' end and Uthappa is in trouble. They go to the TV umpire. Uthappa has to go, he bags a duck. He drops this full ball near short cover and calls for a risky single. Raza sprints to his right, swoops down on the ball and under-arm flicks it onto the furniture. Two wickets in two overs and India slip to 77 for 4

headshotImage.caption: Kedar Jadhav player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Kedar Jadhav player page headshot cutout, 2021

headshotImage.caption: Kedar Jadhav player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Kedar Jadhav player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Kedar Jadhav c †Mutumbami b Chibhabha 5 (13b 1x4 0x6 11m) SR: 38.46

dismissalComment.html: edged and Chibhabha has his second scalp. He is pleased as punch. Back of a length and outside off (not all that short), Jadhav is crease-bound as he aims to cut it away. However, he does not connect properly and nicks it behind. Umpire Tiffin raises his finger again; India are rattled

headshotImage.caption: Donald Tiripano player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Donald Tiripano player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Stuart Binny c †Mutumbami b Tiripano 77 (76b 6x4 2x6 92m) SR: 101.31

dismissalComment.html: Binny swings and edges it behind. Pushed full and wide outside off, Tiripano rolls his fingers across this cutter. Binny's balance is a mess as he looks to kitchen-sink it away. He can only manage an outside edge to Mutumbami. End of a rapid stand, the highest sixth-wicket stand for India

headshotImage.caption: Harbhajan Singh player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Harbhajan Singh player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Vusi Sibanda c Harbhajan Singh b Binny 20 (35b 2x4 1x6 52m) SR: 57.14

dismissalComment.html: Binny strikes back! Dragged short, not much bite in it. It should have been put away, instead Sibanda mis-hits the pull. Harbhajan swallows it at mid-on. Good overhead catch

dismissalText.commentary: Chamu Chibhabha c Rahane b Kumar 3 (12b 0x4 0x6 18m) SR: 25

dismissalComment.html: outswinger with loads of extra extra bounce nabs Chibhabha. He is crease-bound as he spars at it and gets a thickish outside edge, which flies to Rahane at second slip. Good, sharp catch around head height

headshotImage.caption: Axar Patel player page headshot cutout 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Axar Patel player page headshot cutout 2021

headshotImage.caption: Manoj Tiwary player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Manoj Tiwary player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Hamilton Masakadza c Tiwary b Patel 34 (64b 4x4 0x6 66m) SR: 53.12

dismissalComment.html: Hami M falls. Alarming turn and bounce. Might have held up in the pitch as well. Hami M was surprised by it as he just chips it tamely to Tiwary at point off the outside half of the bat. Hami M yanked his bottom hand off the bat as he met the ball

dismissalText.commentary: Elton Chigumbura not out 104 (101b 8x4 1x6 157m) SR: 102.97

headshotImage.caption: Axar Patel player page headshot cutout 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Axar Patel player page headshot cutout 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Sean Williams b Patel 0 (2b 0x4 0x6 7m) SR: 0

dismissalComment.html: Axar takes out Williams for a duck. He gives this more air outside off, grips in the surface and rips through the bat-pad gap to hit the top of middle and off. Zimbabwe fall behind in the chase

headshotImage.caption: Harbhajan Singh player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Harbhajan Singh player page headshot cutout, 2021

headshotImage.caption: Axar Patel player page headshot cutout 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Axar Patel player page headshot cutout 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Sikandar Raza c Patel b Harbhajan Singh 37 (33b 5x4 0x6 31m) SR: 112.12

dismissalComment.html: another half-tracker, Raza goes for a pull and gifts his wicket. He makes a mess of the pull as he mistimes it in the air. Axar runs in from deep midwicket, flings himself forward and snaps it up. First ODI wicket for Harbhajan in four years

headshotImage.caption: Harbhajan Singh player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Harbhajan Singh player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Richmond Mutumbami c Harbhajan Singh b Binny 7 (16b 1x4 0x6 23m) SR: 43.75

dismissalComment.html: Binny rolls his fingers across this one. Mutumbai targets the leg side with a flick but ends up spooning a leading edge to Harbhajan at mid-off. He runs to his right and takes it. They check for a possible no-ball. Binny is okay

dismissalText.commentary: Graeme Cremer c Binny b Kulkarni 27 (36b 2x4 0x6 54m) SR: 75

dismissalComment.html: What have you done Cremer? Full toss outside the leg stump, he goes for a reverse-sweep and hits it right into the lap of  Binny at backward point. The wide has helped him get the wicket, but India needed Chigumbura's wicket
